    "name": "Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis — hemolysis index prediction",
    "description": "A 10,000-sample Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis was performed varying six input parameters (blood viscosity ±15%, power-law hemolysis model coefficients C and α within published uncertainty bounds, inlet velocity profile shape parameter ±10%, mesh resolution factor ±20%, and turbulent Schmidt number 0.7–1.0). Sobol indices indicate that the hemolysis model coefficient C accounts for 52% of output variance in predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), followed by rotational speed uncertainty (18%) and viscosity (14%); geometric and turbulence parameters collectively contribute less than 16% of total variance.",
    "method": "Monte Carlo with Sobol variance decomposition",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "Hemolysis model coefficient C",
      "Rotational speed",
      "Blood viscosity"
    ],
